<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: =
after-white-space;"><div><p data-start=3D"251" data-end=3D"261">Hi =
Zach,</p><p data-start=3D"263" data-end=3D"521">I refer to my Privacy =
Act 2020 requests for full copies of the claim files for C90306048 and =
C90306256 (including all internal notes, reports, third-party =
correspondence, scopes, assessments, emails, phone records, texts, and =
any other relevant materials).</p><p data-start=3D"523" =
data-end=3D"782">Despite my request of 1 July 2025, and my reminder to =
Grant on 27 August 2025, I have not yet received any material. Your =
reference to a 25 July 2025 email or communications is unclear=E2=80=94cou=
ld you kindly resend that correspondence so I have a complete =
record.</p><p data-start=3D"784" data-end=3D"936">Please provide the =
full claim files by&nbsp;<span data-start=3D"823" data-end=3D"859">5:00 =
pm, Monday 1 September 2025</span>, as the 20-working-day timeframe =
under the Privacy Act has already passed.</p><p data-start=3D"938" =
data-end=3D"1301">For ongoing compliance, I would also appreciate =
monthly updates (on the 1st of each month) of the full, up-to-date =
files. If providing full copies each month is difficult, then =
per&nbsp;<strong data-start=3D"1119" data-end=3D"1154">Information =
Privacy Principle 6</strong>, I am happy to receive monthly summaries of =
all new additions, with the complete file provided whenever an =
assessment is submitted or presented.</p><p data-start=3D"1324" =
data-end=3D"1594">In regards to the contents claim, to date, I have only =
received a partial list from David, which does not include item values, =
repair/cleaning details, or assessment of property outside the house =
(including under-deck stairs and deck items, many of which were =
significantly affected by heat and smoke). As more than three months =
have now passed without a complete schedule or proper assessment, I =
would be grateful for an urgent update on this claim.</p><p =
data-start=3D"1765" data-end=3D"2088">Progress on both claims has been =
slower than expected, which is concerning in light of the Code=E2=80=99s =
requirements.</p><p data-start=3D"1765" data-end=3D"2088">In I look =
forward to receiving the comprehensive update from Grant on the house =
claim, as he indicated. As per his request, I am also happy to meet on =
site, and I can make myself available at the following times:</p><ul =
data-start=3D"2090" data-end=3D"2201"><li data-start=3D"2090" =
data-end=3D"2111"><p data-start=3D"2092" data-end=3D"2111">Monday at =
4:00 pm</p></li><li data-start=3D"2112" data-end=3D"2145"><p =
data-start=3D"2114" data-end=3D"2145">Tuesday at 8:00 am or 4:00 =
pm</p></li><li data-start=3D"2146" data-end=3D"2173"><p =
data-start=3D"2148" data-end=3D"2173">Wednesday after 3:30 =
pm</p></li><li data-start=3D"2174" data-end=3D"2201"><p =
data-start=3D"2176" data-end=3D"2201">Thursday before 3:00 =
pm</p></li></ul><p data-start=3D"2203" data-end=3D"2248">Please confirm =
whichever option works best.</p><h3 data-start=3D"2250" =
data-end=3D"2266">Next Steps</h3><p data-start=3D"2267" =
data-end=3D"2404">I trust these matters can be resolved promptly. If =
not, I may need to consider escalating my concerns through the =
appropriate channels.</p><p data-start=3D"2406" data-end=3D"2433">Kind =
regards,<br data-start=3D"2419" data-end=3D"2422">Raffaella</p></div><br =
class=3D"Apple-interchange-newline"><div><div =
